article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 93, Tennessee Tech 75
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Jason McLeish scored a career-high 29 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to a 93-75 win over Tennessee Tech Thursday night. McLeish scored 20 points in the second half for the Colonels (6-7, 3-3 Ohio Valley Conference), who never trailed and led by as many as 19 points in the second half. Matt Witt followed McLeish with 20 points and was 7-of-7 from the free-throw line. Tennessee Tech (8-5, 3-2 OVC) drew to 16-15 with nine minutes remaining in the first half, but Eastern went on a 16-4 run that stretched the margin to 32-19. Mike Rose added 15 points and Alonzo Hird had 14. Anthony Fisher led Tech with 17 points. Milone Clark followed with 13 and Keyon Boyd had 12.
